b'Microwave Mug Cookie Hack :cookie:

Prep Time:\xc2\xa05 minutes
Cook Time: 30-45 seconds
Servings: 1

Ingredients:
4 Squares Nestl\xc3\xa9:registered: Toll House:registered: Refrigerated Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough
1 TBS Nestl\xc3\xa9:registered: Toll House:registered: Semi Sweet Morsels
1 Scoop Vanilla Ice Cream

Directions:

Break up the cookie dough into almond sized pieces and place into microwave-safe mug. Top with morsels. Microwave on high setting for 45 seconds in an 800watt machine or for 30 seconds in a 1200watt machine.

Carefully remove mug from microwave. Let mug sit for 2 minutes, then top with a scoop of ice cream. *Please note that the cookie will be hot. Take caution when eating.

#NestleTollHouse #TollHouse #Hacks #EasyRecipes #MugCake #MicrowaveCake #EasyDessert #ChocolateChipCookie #Cookies #FoodHacks'

b'Dip, Dunk, Devour! :cookie:

Chocolate Chip Cookie Dippers
Yield: Approximately 14 cookies

Ingredients:
12 Squares Nestl\xc3\xa9:registered: Toll House:registered: Refrigerated Chocolate Chip OR Sugar Cookie Dough
\xc2\xbd Cup Store-bought Chocolate or Cream Cheese Icing
2 TBS Nestl\xc3\xa9:registered: Toll House:registered: Mini Morsels (optional)

Directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350\xc2\xb0F. Set aside 1 baking tray.

2. Place the cookie dough on a piece of parchment or wax paper. Using a rolling pin, roll the cookie dough to \xc2\xbc inch thick. Place the dough in the freezer for 10 minutes.

3. Take the dough out of the freezer and cut the dough into small shapes with cookie cutters of your choice, or into 1.5 inch triangles.

4. Bake cookies for 5-6 minutes, until the edges are golden brown.

5. Remove tray from oven and let cool on a cooling rack for 5 minutes. Then place cookies directly on the cooling rack and cool completely.\xc2\xa0

6. Place icing in a small serving dish enjoy the cookies as dippers.

#NestleTollHouse #TollHouse #EasyRecipes #CookieRecipe #ChocolateChipCookies #Cookies #SnackTime #KidsRecipes #KidApproved #:cookie:'

b'Halloween Trash Cookies Recipe :jack-o-lantern::ghost:

Why choose between Halloween candy or cookies when you can have both, in one!?

Yield: Approximately 24 cookies
Prep Time: 15 Minutes
Bake Time: 11 Minutes

Ingredients:
2 \xc2\xbc Cup All Purpose Flour
1 tsp. Baking Soda
1 tsp. Salt
1 cup (2 sticks) Unsalted Butter, room temp.
\xc2\xbe Cup Granulated Sugar
\xc2\xbe Cup Light Brown Sugar
1 tsp. Vanilla Extract
2 Large Eggs
1/3 Cup Nestl\xc3\xa9:registered: Toll House:registered: Semi Sweet Morsels
1/3 Cup Nestl\xc3\xa9:registered: Toll House:registered: Butterscotch Morsels
\xc2\xbc Cup Candy Corn
\xc2\xbd Cup Crushed Potato Chips or Pretzels, chopped
1/3 Cup Chopped Candy Bar or other Chocolate Halloween Candy, chopped

*Additional candies and/or chips for decoration.

Directions:
Preheat oven to 375\xc2\xb0F. Set aside baking trays.

In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.

In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla extract and mix until combined. Beat in flour mixture gradually. Stir in morsels, candies, and potato chips.

Use a large cookie scoop, or \xc2\xbc cup measurer, to drop dough on to sheet trays. Place additional candies and chips on top of cookies, if desired.

Bake 10-12 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool on baking sheets for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.

*NOTE: Candy Corn has a tendency to melt in the oven. If this is not desired in your cookies, do not add them to the tops of the cookies.

#NestleTollHouse #TollHouse #Halloween #HalloweenRecipe #CookieRecipe #Cookies #EasyRecipe #Recipe #SpookySeason #BakeFeed'

b'What are you looking at?! :eyes:

Halloween Eyeball Monster Cookie Recipe

Yield: Approximately 30-36 cookies
Prep Time: 15 Minutes
Bake Time: 11 Minutes

Ingredients:
2 \xc2\xbc Cup All Purpose Flour
2/3 cup NESTL\xc3\x89:registered: TOLL HOUSE:registered: Baking Cocoa
1 tsp. baking soda
\xc2\xbc tsp salt
1 cup (2 sticks) salted butter softened
\xc2\xbe cup granulated sugar
2/3 cup light brown sugar
2 large eggs
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 Cup NESTL\xc3\x89:registered: TOLL HOUSE:registered: Mini Morsels
1 Cup Decorative Candy Eyeballs

Directions:

PREHEAT oven to 350\xc2\xb0 F. Set aside 2 ungreased baking trays.

COMBINE flour, cocoa, baking soda, and salt in small bowl. Beat butter and sugars in large mixer bowl until creamy. Add eggs and extract, beating well. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in mini morsels. Using a cookie scoop or TBS measurer, scoop dough into balls and place on baking trays.

PLACE candy eyeballs decoratively on tops of cookies.

BAKE for 9 to 11 minutes or until centers are set. Cool on baking sheets for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.

#NestleTollHouse #TollHouse #Halloween #HalloweenRecipe #CookieRecipe #Cookies #EasyRecipe\xc2\xa0#Recipe #SpookySeason #BakeFeed'

b'Funfetti:registered: Cloud Bread, this is what dreams are made of! :cloud::rainbow::party_popper:

Nestl\xc3\xa9:registered: Toll House:registered: Funfetti:registered: Morsel Cloud Bread
Yield: 6 Servings
Prep Time: 10 Minutes
Bake Time: 30 Minutes

Ingredients:
4 Large Egg Whites
2 \xc2\xbd TBS Granulated Sugar
1 TBS Cornstarch
\xc2\xbc tsp Vanilla Extract
1 \xc2\xbd TBS Rainbow Sprinkles, divided
1/3 Cup Nestl\xc3\xa9:registered: Toll House:registered: Funfetti:registered: Morsels
Optional: 2-3 Drops Food coloring.

Directions:

PREHEAT oven to 300\xc2\xb0F. Spray a baking tray with baking spray or line with parchment.

USE a large mixer bowl with the whisk attachment, or hand-held mixer, to whip egg whites until white and frothy. Slowly add the granulated sugar, followed by the corn starch and extract. Continue whipping egg whites to stiff peaks.

ADD food coloring, if using.

STIR in 1 TBS sprinkles and all of the Funfetti:registered: Morsels. Gently pour the meringue on to prepared baking pan, creating a circular mound of the batter in the center of the tray, approximately 8 inches in diameter. Sprinkle remaining sprinkles on top of meringue.

BAKE 25-30 minutes until outside is browned and meringue is soft but cooked through.

REMOVE from oven and cool tray on cooling rack until room temperature. Cut bread prior to serving.

*Cloud bread may slightly deflate or become slightly wrinkly in texture once removed from the oven. \xc2\xa0This is expected and due to the high level of egg whites in the dish.

#nestletollhouse #tollhouse #cloudbread #funfetti #sprinkles #recipe #simplerecipe #easyrecipe #reels #bakefeed #asmr'
